            <h2>About Đắk Lắk</h2>
            <p>Đắk Lắk is a province located in the Central Highlands of Vietnam. Known for its rich cultural heritage and diverse natural landscapes, Đắk Lắk offers a unique experience for visitors. The province is home to various ethnic groups, each contributing to the vibrant local culture.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Key Attractions</h2>
            <h3>Yok Đôn National Park</h3>
            <p>One of the largest national parks in Vietnam, Yok Đôn is known for its diverse flora and fauna, and is a haven for wildlife enthusiasts.</p>
            <h3>Buôn Đôn Village</h3>
            <p>A traditional village famous for its elephant hunting and taming heritage, Buôn Đôn offers a glimpse into the unique customs and lifestyle of the local people.</p>
            <h3>Dray Nur Waterfall</h3>
            <p>Known for its stunning beauty, Dray Nur Waterfall is a must-visit destination for nature lovers and photographers.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Cultural Heritage</h2>
            <p>Đắk Lắk is rich in cultural traditions, with many festivals, dances, and crafts that reflect the province's history and the influences of its various ethnic groups.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Visitor Information</h2>
            <p>Getting to Đắk Lắk is easy with regular flights to Buon Ma Thuot Airport from major cities. The province offers a range of accommodations from budget to luxury, catering to all types of travelers.</p>
        </section>
